<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>JavaScript Learning</h2>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Debitis sint esse culpa,
             dolores aliquid molestiae, quas repellendus placeat dicta laborum nostrum eum eveniet iste
             reprehenderit unde deserunt laudantium reiciendis fuga!</p>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Laboriosam natus iste nemo nesciunt, nostrum vero vitae sit possimus blanditiis
                 esse saepe reiciendis cumque, excepturi eaque veritatis modi praesentium rerum sequi.</p>
        <button id="btn">Toggle Dark Mode</button>
    </div>
     
    <script>
        // Fixed the error by accessing the first element of the collection
        const containerDiv = document.getElementsByClassName('container')[0];
        const toggleBtn = document.getElementById('btn');
        
        toggleBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
            // Toggle dark class on the container
            containerDiv.classList.toggle('dark');
            
            // Toggle dark mode on the body as well
            document.body.classList.toggle('dark-mode');
            
            // Update button text based on current mode
            if (containerDiv.classList.contains('dark')) {
                toggleBtn.textContent = 'Toggle Light Mode';
            } else {
                toggleBtn.textContent = 'Toggle Dark Mode';
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
